Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1045 "The Birthday \NParty of Divine Punishment (Part One)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[op]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,[ed]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,[eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.85,Bookstore,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Yamai Bookstore
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.32,0:00:02.54,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.10,0:00:06.36,Doremi,SIGN PINK,0000,0000,0000,,Doremi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.29,0:00:06.36,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's Sekizawa Remi's photobook "Doremi."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.20,0:00:06.36,Photobook,SIGN RED,0000,0000,0000,,Sekizawa Remi's 1st Photobook
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.72,0:00:08.78,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we got the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.78,0:00:10.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.06,0:00:12.57,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister sure is popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.57,0:00:13.61,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.82,0:00:17.70,Yumi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Sekizawa Yumi (17) \NTeitan High School 2nd Year
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.42,0:00:19.62,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Although to me, she's just \Nmy clumsy slob of a sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.86,0:00:25.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the detective's assistant she \Nplayed in that recent drama was cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.06,0:00:28.31,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,She was a terrible assistant lacking \Nin detective skills, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.31,0:00:30.71,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, that's a script issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:33.38,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, her main job is modeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.61,0:00:37.09,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you sure we can go tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.09,0:00:39.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,To Sekizawa Remi's birthday party.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.66,0:00:41.39,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we're ordinary people?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.59,0:00:42.46,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.46,0:00:47.70,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a little party we're holding at a \Nrestaurant my sister's classmate works at.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.70,0:00:50.40,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And it's actually my birthday party, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.80,0:00:55.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Your birthday's two days \Nafter Valentines Day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.83,0:00:58.40,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, February 16th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.40,0:01:00.83,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Since my sister's birthday is \Nthe day after Valentines Day,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.83,0:01:03.59,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,we've celebrated them \Ntogether since we were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.08,0:01:08.58,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, there's another \Nreason I want you guys to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.90,0:01:11.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.45,0:01:13.45,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.45,0:01:15.26,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.46,0:01:19.01,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Yumi-chin, about that \Nthing I mentioned earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.18,0:01:20.21,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.21,0:01:23.14,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He's a boy in first grade, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.14,0:01:24.27,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.27,0:01:27.43,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it'll be fine if there's \None extra kid at the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.64,0:01:30.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It comes to visit after falling asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.11,0:01:32.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Fall in love with logical deduction \Nand the pleasure of solving mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.20,0:01:33.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the birthday party of a popular model!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.74,0:01:35.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A scream rings out when \Nthe cake is brought out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.87,0:01:37.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:39.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.33,0:01:41.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.97,0:03:29.98,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,1)}The Birthday Party of Divine Punishment \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.54,0:03:27.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Birthday Party of Divine \NPunishment, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.42,0:03:45.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The restaurant isn't that big.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.04,0:03:48.54,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But everyone here is a \Nmodel, actor, or celebrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.54,0:03:51.56,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder everyone's so fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.56,0:03:54.63,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you glad you got \Nto come, too, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.35,0:03:59.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? You don't seem well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:04.26,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun has a mouth ulcer so \Nit's hard for him to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:07.45,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you remember to bring your medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.45,0:04:09.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,'eah, I brough' ih.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.24,0:04:13.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You should've left the kid at \Nhome if he had a mouth ulcer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.01,0:04:17.31,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but my dad has a neighborhood \Nassociation meeting tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:20.32,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun would've had to stay home alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.72,0:04:24.41,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you take your medicine \Nbefore the party starts?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.41,0:04:25.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,O-hay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.96,0:04:29.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see. I think I'm supposed \Nto take one tablet at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.69,0:04:36.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I put my mouth ulcer medicine in \Nthe case I was keeping that medicine in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.26,0:04:38.09,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.29,0:04:39.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:42.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What's that blue and white capsule?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.14,0:04:45.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nu-hing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.27,0:04:52.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I can tell her it's the APTX-4869 \Nantidote Haibara gave me on our school trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.73,0:04:59.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and that I've been secretly \Nholding onto the spare capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.21,0:05:04.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Does the kid not like \Nmedicine or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.01,0:05:06.50,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.85,0:05:08.70,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.45,0:05:13.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,As we thought, Conan-kun \Nhad some kind of medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.31,0:05:20.86,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,I see. But if it was white and blue, \Nthen it's not the poison I was given.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:28.22,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by his flustered reaction, it's \Nlikely an antidote that would restore my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.90,0:05:30.74,DCMain,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Steal it if you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.74,0:05:32.39,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.37,0:05:35.15,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.68,0:05:39.48,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,They force-fed me a red and white capsule
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.26,0:05:44.90,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,when I was beaten on \NVauxhall Bridge in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.35,0:05:51.10,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,So you're my sister Yumi's classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:53.49,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ran-chan, Sonoko-chan, and Sera-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.66,0:05:55.25,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.45,0:05:58.75,Remi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Sekizawa Remi (21) \NModel
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.44,0:05:58.75,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Enjoy yourselves today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:03.64,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, um... I bought your photobook today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.64,0:06:05.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could I get your autograph later?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.93,0:06:08.40,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can take care of that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:12.15,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kushiyama-san, could you hand me \Nthe permanent marker in my bag?{\an8}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.47,0:06:12.97,Kushiyama,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460}Kushiyama Mitomu (28) \NRemi's Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:13.26,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.26,0:06:15.90,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:17.49,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.99,0:06:19.66,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is "To Ran-chan" okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.66,0:06:21.92,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.92,0:06:22.94,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.42,0:06:24.36,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:26.61,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,This marker doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:30.74,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I smelled thinner when I \Nopened your bag just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:33.04,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the cap came off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:34.16,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:34.87,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.11,0:06:38.61,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You never put the cap back on tightly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.61,0:06:40.69,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Here, I've got a spare permanent marker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:41.88,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Nice one, Yumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.41,0:06:42.85,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.85,0:06:45.26,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thanks for waiting. Sonoko-chan, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.19,0:06:45.56,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yumi-chin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.26,0:06:46.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It's Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.31,0:06:48.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who can we talk to for some water?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.73,0:06:51.05,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,This kid wants to take his medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.32,0:06:52.33,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.33,0:06:54.22,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get you some.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:55.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.90,0:06:59.34,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,If you have any allergies, I'll let \Nthe staff know while I'm at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.34,0:07:00.71,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,None in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.71,0:07:01.76,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.76,0:07:02.94,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.95,0:07:10.21,ToRan,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,To Ran-chan
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.37,0:07:06.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I'll treasure this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.07,0:07:07.40,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:11.13,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, sis. You shouldn't \Nstick a pen there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:12.70,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It'll leave a weird stain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.05,0:07:15.01,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,But what if someone else \Nasks me for my autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.01,0:07:17.77,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hold onto it for you until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.77,0:07:20.02,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You can't tell who's the older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.02,0:07:20.86,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.86,0:07:23.21,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,They've been like that since they were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.67,0:07:26.32,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi-chan's four years younger, but \Nshe's always been more put together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.32,0:07:30.22,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,I genuinely believed it was Yumi-chan \Nwho applied to the modeling job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.42,0:07:34.30,Hatsune,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Hatsune Tsuguo (21) \NPastry Chef
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.53,0:07:35.24,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, I'm Remi's middle and high \Nschool classmate Hatsune Tsuguo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.72,0:07:38.97,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a pastry chef who hopes to \Nopen his own restaurant someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.44,0:07:44.90,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,I asked the chef to let me make the birthday \Ncake for today, so you won't want to miss that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.90,0:07:45.78,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.78,0:07:47.24,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:52.02,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You want to become an independent \Npastry chef and open your own shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.02,0:07:53.62,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.62,0:07:55.62,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.82,0:07:59.75,Hanasaki,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Hanasaki Mizutoshi (32) \NHair and Makeup Artist
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.85,0:08:02.38,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Maybe your cakes will sell if you say \Nthey're made by Sekizawa Remi's classmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.81,0:08:05.70,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.70,0:08:09.26,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, Remi-chan. Happy birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:11.77,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hanasaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.77,0:08:14.48,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Here, a bouquet for your birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.48,0:08:15.64,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.79,0:08:17.20,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thank you, Hanasaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:18.72,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the creep?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.20,0:08:18.72,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.72,0:08:20.39,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hanasaki Mizutoshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.76,0:08:23.73,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He's a hair and makeup artist \Nwho's hit on and been rejected
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:26.54,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,by my sister a bunch of times \Ndespite having a wife and kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.54,0:08:28.57,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What a scumbag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.79,0:08:30.95,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you wearing those glasses for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.95,0:08:32.82,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.02,0:08:36.11,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, he even \Nhit on me the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.11,0:08:38.58,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Just ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.82,0:08:41.62,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But he's a good hair and makeup artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:43.59,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't totally disregard him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.59,0:08:47.02,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's why you invited us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.02,0:08:49.73,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,To prevent him from hitting on you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.73,0:08:50.59,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.94,0:08:53.50,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And it's easier to avoid \Nhim if I'm with friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.50,0:08:56.07,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. We'll protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.07,0:08:57.44,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.44,0:08:58.60,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.98,0:09:03.20,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's got nothing to worry about with \Na Jeet Kune Do expert, karate master,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.20,0:09:06.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the Suzuki conglomerate protecting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.53,0:09:06.60,Conglomerate,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(460,1)}Suzuki Conglomerate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.35,0:09:14.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was great.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.30,0:09:16.07,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That just leaves dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:18.84,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for that birthday cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:20.33,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.12,0:09:25.62,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Happy birthday to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.62,0:09:29.13,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Happy birthday to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.39,0:09:35.43,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Happy birthday dear Remi and Yumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.43,0:09:40.28,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Happy birthday to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.00,0:09:48.59,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Your glasses are glowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.59,0:09:51.40,DCMain,HANASAKI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? Pretty cool, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.59,0:09:55.23,DCItalic,MC,0000,0000,0000,,While the cake is being distributed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.23,0:09:58.91,DCItalic,MC,0000,0000,0000,,please enjoy some of Remi \Nand Yumi's favorite photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:04.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi-chin is so tiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.66,0:10:07.40,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.17,0:10:09.14,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.14,0:10:10.23,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.68,0:10:12.62,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:18.47,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:20.78,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Three second rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.78,0:10:22.00,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.19,0:10:30.58,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did someone collapse?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.58,0:10:32.31,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Was it that hair and makeup guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.11,0:10:36.69,DCMain,WAITER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I broke a wine bottle!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.69,0:10:38.87,DCMain,WAITER,0000,0000,0000,,Please stay away from this area!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.87,0:10:40.98,DCMain,MAN A,0000,0000,0000,,This area?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.98,0:10:41.87,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,What area?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.62,0:10:44.52,DCMain,WOMAN B,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, someone turn on the lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.52,0:10:47.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. It's too dark to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.77,0:10:52.75,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hanasaki-san's glowing glasses \Nare coming in and out of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.20,0:10:55.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone by his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.12,0:10:56.24,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.76,0:11:10.94,Punishment,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Divine Punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:16.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Poisoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.21,0:11:22.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The victim Hanasaki Mizutoshi-san \Nate something poisoned and died?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:24.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, according to forensics,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.28,0:11:31.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,the cake the victim ate before he \Ncollapsed was probably poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:38.88,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We even found a small bottle containing \Ncyanide taped beneath the table at the victim's seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.61,0:11:42.78,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But how did the culprit \Ndo that during a party?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.78,0:11:47.67,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He apparently collapsed while photos \Nwere being shown using that projector.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.67,0:11:49.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It was dimly lit inside the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:54.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The restaurant may have been dimly lit,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.52,0:11:59.03,Punishment,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Divine Punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.97,0:11:59.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but wouldn't someone have seen a person \Nwriting on the victim's forehead
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:02.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,with a permanent marker?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.04,0:12:05.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately after the victim collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.29,0:12:11.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,the projector suddenly turned \Noff, and the room became pitch dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.90,0:12:14.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But if it was pitch dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.21,0:12:19.96,Punishment,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Divine Punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:17.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,then how did someone write \Nthese letters on his forehead?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.26,0:12:22.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim's glasses were a novelty \Nitem that glowed in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.79,0:12:23.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:28.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So it would be possible to write by touch if \Nthe culprit knew where the victim's head was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.97,0:12:35.73,Punishment,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Divine Punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:31.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Since the writing is rather distorted,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.65,0:12:35.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,it seems they used their non-dominant \Nhand to disguise their handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.07,0:12:40.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But between the guests and staff, there are \Nclose to 40 people inside the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.93,0:12:44.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Identifying the culprit won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.19,0:12:46.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,'ere are 'our 'uspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:47.82,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,'uspects?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.14,0:12:51.58,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I think he's trying to say, \N"There are four suspects."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.06,0:12:53.50,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:12:57.91,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Our classmate's sister is \NSekizawa Remi-san the model.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.91,0:13:02.01,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,We were invited to her birthday party.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.24,0:13:05.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's this about four suspects?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.93,0:13:07.51,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.75,0:13:12.68,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The left side of the victim was blocked \Nby the projector and our seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.95,0:13:15.56,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,And the right side of the \Nvictim—well, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.99,0:13:18.94,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,An employee dropped and broke \Na wine bottle in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.94,0:13:23.11,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The floor is covered in wine, but there's \Nno sign anyone stepped through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.11,0:13:27.32,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,And the kitchen is through the \Ndoor past the victim's head,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.68,0:13:32.47,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,but the kitchen staff said \Nnobody came through the door
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.47,0:13:37.08,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,between the time the projector \Nturned off and the lights came on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.31,0:13:43.17,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this murder \Nscene was a closed space
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.17,0:13:46.47,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,nobody could leave once the victim \Nate the poisoned cake and collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.86,0:13:53.49,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Excluding us, who didn't know the victim, \Nthere were only four people in that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.49,0:13:56.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So, who are those four?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.24,0:14:02.15,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,We're having them wait in the corner of the \Nroom so they can't take anything out of the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.05,0:14:06.86,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,These four are the suspects who \Ncould've poisoned the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.86,0:14:08.24,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.41,0:14:10.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi-chin's a suspect, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.27,0:14:12.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Keep her out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.06,0:14:16.25,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's just for now. After all, \Nshe seems to know the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.25,0:14:17.75,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.28,0:14:19.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,'eah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.56,0:14:23.46,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? Your cold \Nsore hasn't healed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:26.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you should have more of that medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.27,0:14:27.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm 'ine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.86,0:14:35.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, we'll let the other guests \Nleave and speak to each of you individually
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.30,0:14:37.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,about your relationship with the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.30,0:14:42.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and what you were doing before \Nand after the victim collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.18,0:14:46.94,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,The late Hanasaki-san was \Na hair and makeup artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:50.61,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,He did most of my hair and makeup.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.05,0:14:55.06,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Since he was skilled and popular, \NI appreciated his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.06,0:14:58.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So your relationship was \Nstrictly professional?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:14:59.62,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.90,0:15:03.06,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Though he did hit on me several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.06,0:15:07.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hit on you? Wasn't Hanasaki-san married?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.93,0:15:09.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Was he cheating?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.51,0:15:12.22,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I turned him down every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:14.39,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I figured he was half-joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.66,0:15:15.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.81,0:15:18.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So, what were you doing during the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.41,0:15:21.45,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hanasaki-san was wearing the glowing glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.45,0:15:25.40,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,I commented on his glasses and was \Neating the cake that was brought to me
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.72,0:15:28.57,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,when Hanasaki-san suddenly \Nstood up and collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.38,0:15:33.38,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't leave my seat after \Nthat until the lights turned on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.38,0:15:36.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So you didn't do anything besides eat cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.21,0:15:41.94,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,It was dim inside the restaurant so \Nphotos could be shown on the projector,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.94,0:15:44.79,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,and I dropped the strawberry \Non my cake onto the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.15,0:15:47.71,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I saw that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.90,0:15:52.76,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,She said, "three second rule," \Nand ate the strawberry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.97,0:15:55.25,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Three second rule?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.25,0:15:57.00,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't need to mention that part.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.00,0:15:57.76,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.30,0:16:02.13,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So, Yumi-san, were you next to \Nyour sister the entire time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.13,0:16:03.05,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.05,0:16:08.17,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I love cake, so after scarfing mine \Ndown, I tried to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.17,0:16:11.28,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's when Hanasaki-san \Ngroaned and collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.55,0:16:15.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't rush to his side?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.02,0:16:17.24,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No. It was pitch black,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.57,0:16:20.91,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,and someone said a wine \Nbottle had broken nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:24.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So you weren't close with the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.17,0:16:25.26,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.26,0:16:28.98,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He hit on me several times as \Nwell, but I rejected his advances.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.98,0:16:30.51,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.85,0:16:31.85,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.66,0:16:35.76,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I frequently met Hanasaki-san on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.10,0:16:39.41,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he did the hair and \Nmakeup for the model I manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.88,0:16:43.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So you never experienced any \Nproblems with the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.97,0:16:49.60,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,As she mentioned earlier, he was a skilled \Nand popular hair and makeup artist,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.60,0:16:53.53,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,so he did make several demands in \Nexchange for prioritizing Sekizawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:55.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What demands?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.40,0:16:58.91,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Like asking to know her \Nfavorite flowers and foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.44,0:17:03.04,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Or in this case, requesting \Nto be seated next to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.36,0:17:06.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What were you doing during the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.00,0:17:10.80,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I received a phone call during that time, \Nso I left my seat before eating my cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.06,0:17:15.34,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,And to prove it, look. You can \Nsee my cake hasn't been touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:16.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.53,0:17:19.88,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Hanasaki-san collapsed \Nwhile I was on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.88,0:17:23.09,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,The lights turned on, \Nand then police arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.09,0:17:26.63,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't returned to my seat since \Nleaving it to take a phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.24,0:17:31.57,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm the one who made this cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:35.48,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Since it was my middle and high school \Nclassmate Remi's birthday party,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.48,0:17:38.07,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,I asked the chef to allow me to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:42.83,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who cut the cake and brought \Na piece to the victim, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.83,0:17:46.15,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I put a strawberry \Non each and every piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.64,0:17:48.58,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Strawberries are Remi's favorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:51.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know the victim Hanasaki-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.26,0:17:53.84,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,No, today was the first time I met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.32,0:17:57.05,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Although I had heard from Yumi-chan \Nthat he was bothering Remi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:17:59.34,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,by persistently hitting on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.60,0:18:02.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What were you doing during the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.32,0:18:05.48,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,It suddenly became pitch black while I \Nwas cutting and distributing the cake,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:08.80,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,so I held onto the cart the cake \Nwas on until the lights came on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.33,0:18:11.29,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,so no one would bump into \Nit and knock it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.12,0:18:15.63,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, wouldn't it be faster \Nto examine our belongings?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.63,0:18:17.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.29,0:18:18.66,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about the pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:22.29,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit wrote something on \Nthat Hanasaki guy's forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.29,0:18:25.62,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever has that pen now must've done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.94,0:18:27.91,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I don't have a pen on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:30.92,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to check your pockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.89,0:18:38.31,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem to have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.31,0:18:41.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Manager, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.33,0:18:46.11,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I normally \Nhold onto Sekizawa's bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.11,0:18:49.14,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,She generally keeps a permanent \Nmarker in it for writing autographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.73,0:18:51.27,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't work, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.19,0:18:54.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.76,0:18:57.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The inside of this bag smells like thinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.31,0:19:00.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you didn't leave the cap off \Nafter the murder so it would become unusable?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.29,0:19:05.28,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Before the party started, Sekizawa tried \Nto give her autograph to that girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.28,0:19:06.78,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,but the pen didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.78,0:19:08.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.22,0:19:09.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.33,0:19:11.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So you didn't get her autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.95,0:19:16.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I did. Yumi-chin had a spare permanent \Nmarker, so she used that instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.98,0:19:20.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So currently Remi-san has a working marker?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.90,0:19:23.68,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,No, this must be a mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.74,0:19:22.70,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.01,0:19:26.73,DCMain,KUSHIYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way Sekizawa would kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.73,0:19:29.22,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,I returned the marker to my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.22,0:19:32.69,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's true. The pen is inside my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.15,0:19:35.45,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.45,0:19:37.29,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't kill anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.29,0:19:38.69,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.05,0:19:41.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sera-chan, do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.48,0:19:43.77,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.18,0:19:47.28,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's my mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.28,0:19:48.83,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, just a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.83,0:19:49.87,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:51.75,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.52,0:19:56.41,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Do you think you'll \Nbe able to get the medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.41,0:20:00.16,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was poisoned at the restaurant \Nwhere the party's being held.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.16,0:20:01.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time for that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.12,0:20:04.02,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call you back later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.31,0:20:06.26,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.08,0:20:08.36,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Poisoned, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.39,0:20:26.28,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,You're late,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.59,0:20:28.67,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Tsutomu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.17,0:20:30.43,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.13,0:20:36.41,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,It's been so long, I had a hard time \Nremembering our usual meeting spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:39.30,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,I'd completely forgotten \Nit was by the railing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:43.55,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,on the Vauxhall Bridge right \Nin front of the SIS Building.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.09,0:20:48.54,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you figure out \Nwho killed Haneda Koji?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.54,0:20:49.42,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.16,0:20:53.54,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,I was only able to determine that \Nit was a large organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.31,0:20:57.81,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,Running away from them once I'd caught \Ntheir attention took everything I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:02.58,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you contact me for over a decade?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.21,0:21:07.14,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,I told you when we ran into each \Nother in town the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.57,0:21:11.15,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,I suffered a major head injury \Nwhile fleeing from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.15,0:21:14.78,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,I'd been wandering around town in \Na state of amnesia for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.57,0:21:19.00,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,My memories finally returned \Nbecause I met you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.43,0:21:22.44,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,I should be able to resume my \Nduties with MI6 a year from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.77,0:21:27.31,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, did you \Ncome here with the boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.92,0:21:32.35,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's just me and our daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.65,0:21:33.60,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,Daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.14,0:21:39.11,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,You mean you still don't \Nremember the daughter you held?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.40,0:21:41.52,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.04,0:21:43.30,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,Is she a big girl now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.19,0:21:48.33,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Mary?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.89,0:21:50.24,DCItalic,TSUTOMU,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.78,0:21:58.88,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,When Tsutomu-san and I parted ways, \Nmy daughter was still inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.36,0:22:00.50,DCItalic,MARY,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.24,0:22:10.35,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.10,0:22:14.52,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not Akai Tsutomu.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.85,0:22:23.49,DCItalic,VERMOUTH,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the woman who's about to \Nkill you using this poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.41,0:23:49.35,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Yumi-kun's the only one \Nwho had a working marker.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.03,0:23:52.70,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It makes sense they'd suspect her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.91,0:23:57.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't she a little far away \Nto have poisoned the cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.81,0:24:01.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know if there was anyone who may \Nhave held a grudge against the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.23,0:24:03.25,DCMain,YUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.25,0:24:04.96,DCMain,REMI,0000,0000,0000,,More than I can count.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.38,0:24:07.21,DCMain,HATSUNE,0000,0000,0000,,He was a serial complainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.21,0:24:08.68,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,The Birthday Party of Divine Punishment \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.31,0:24:13.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The Birthday \NParty of Divine Punishment, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Permanent Marker
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.26,0:24:32.65,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.65,0:24:34.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A 'ermanent 'arker!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:36.08,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Huh? What'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.08,0:24:37.80,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Permanent marker, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.80,0:24:39.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}'anks, Ran-neechan.
